The paper deals with machine learning methods, specifically robust regression using SVM and ELM algorithms. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of kernel-based regression algorithms also suggests a possible fit under neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) subcategories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of iterative reweighted methods, which could also be relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) subcategory.
